In summary, in this work we propose a universal quan-
tum Otto heat machine (UQOHM) based on the open
Dicke model (ODM). The ODM is composed of N atoms
of two levels (qubits) that interact with a mode of the
electromagnetic field and both the mode and the N
qubits, which constitute the working substance of the
universal machine, interact with thermal reservoirs. This
model presents a critical point and can be solved analyt-
